
 For 1.0
 -------

. Add vstr_parse_double()/long_double()

. Allow non-atomic ops.

. Way to delete from a section and have section pos/len updates ... use cache ?

. _conv_sub_buf_buf() ? ...
   Ie. vstr_conv_sub_buf_buf(s1, 1, s1->len, "\t", 1, "    ", 4)

. parse_ipv6
 *   1. hhhh:hhhh:hhhh:hhhh:hhhh:hhhh:hhhh:hhhh
 *   2. any number of 0000 may be abbreviated as "::", but only once
 *   3. The last two words may be written as IPv4 address
  include CIDR

. VSTR_FLAG_PARSE_NUM_LOC_SEP

. Man page equiv. for constants.html

. http://burtleburtle.net/bob/hash/doobs.html .. vstr_hash ?

. $*.*{blah:%u} ... gives a gcc warning
  $*.*{blah:%*.*u} .. is ok, but that requires 4 string entries instead of 1.

